  "routing": {
    "sender": "scott-wlaschin",
    "senderColor": "purple",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "yellow",
    "summary": "Aligned with your task breakdown, commit discipline",
    "content": "Kent, I've sent the team lead my final position on the task breakdown. I'm converging with your proposal: add both \"base template + static serving\" and \"session infrastructure\" as explicit tasks between the walking skeleton and US-1.\n\nMy reasoning: the base template is a shared foundation (like design tokens), and session infrastructure is cross-cutting plumbing that three features depend on. Both deserve focused attention and separate commits.\n\nThe domain types (ValidatedEmail, Password, UserId, User) will emerge from TDD during the feature tasks, not as separate tasks. This aligns with our agreement that tests pull types into existence.\n\nOne thing I want to be clear about for the rebuild: **every green step gets committed immediately.** We learned this the hard way. The TDD cycle is now: Red -> Green -> COMMIT -> Refactor -> COMMIT. No exceptions.\n\nAre you aligned with this task breakdown?"
  }
}
